    "instructions_important": "false",
    "long_instructions": "### Nested Loops\r\n\r\nColin noticed that this song has two repeating sections. Instead of writing the same code over and over, he could use a **nested loop** to make his code simpler and more efficient!\r\n\r\n![](https://images.code.org/202b3dbd1c35dfa7ee594f8e2c8d79fa-image-1745009401512.png)\r\n\r\nCan you recreate Colin’s code using a nested loop? All the blocks you need are already in the workspace.\r\n\r\n> ***Hint:*** Not all of the code belongs inside the loop. Take a look at what repeats and where!\r\n\r\nUse **pattern recognition** to prepare:\r\n- What sections of the song repeat? Try to spot them in the code.\r\n- Which blocks appear more than once?\r\n- Do any instruments or tracks follow the same pattern over and over?",
